  "texts": [
    "When the AR-enabled game Pokémon Go first debuted in 2016, it allowed players to interact with Pokémon characters by superimposing them onto their environment using their smartphone cameras.",
    "AR technology can be delivered through smartphones, screens, glasses, head mount displays, and AR software.",
    "There are two main categories of AR, which include marker-based and markerless AR.",
    "Marker-based AR applications utilize image recognition to detect a marker, an object that triggers the AR application.",
    "On the other hand, markerless AR applications do not require markers and allow users to choose the location where they want to display digital content."
  ],
